        "id": "salah-niyyah",
        "title": "The Theology and Articulation of Niyyah",
        "icon": "ğŸ’­",
        "body": "<h4>The Theology and Articulation of Niyyah (Intention)</h4>\n<p>In Islamic jurisprudence, the intention, universally known as the Niyyah, is the vital psychological and spiritual mechanism that separates a mundane daily action from an act of divine worship. The Niyyah is fundamentally an act of the heart and mind; knowing precisely which prayer is being offered, its specific timing, and its exact Rakat (unit) count is technically sufficient to fulfill the requirement. If a person stands with the clear mental recognition that they are about to perform the four obligatory Rakats of the Dhuhr prayer, the Niyyah is achieved.</p>\n<p>However, vocalizing the intention has become a widely accepted and highly recommended practice to assist beginners in cementing their focus and eliminating distracting thoughts before speaking to the Divine. The structural formula for a verbal Niyyah generally dictates the type of prayer (Fard, Sunnah, Nafl), the specific time of day (Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, or Isha), the exact number of Rakats, and the physical direction of the Qiblah.</p>\n<p>To guide an unaware first-timer, the following table exhaustively catalogs the precise verbal Niyyahs for the various daily prayers and their specific combinations. If a worshipper is praying behind an Imam in a congregation, they must silently append the phrase \"I follow this Imam\" (e.g., eqtadaitu bihÄzal imÄmi) to their intention.</p>\n<div style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"><table class=\"salah-table\"><thead><tr><th>Salah Time</th><th>Prayer Type & Rakat Count</th><th>Transliterated Arabic Niyyah</th><th>English Translation</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Fajr</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil Fajr sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Fajr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Fajr</td><td>2 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil Fajr fardullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Fajr Fard (Obligatory), facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtiz Zuhr sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Dhuhr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtiz Zuhr fardullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Dhuhr Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtiz Zuhr sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Dhuhr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dhuhr</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtiz Zuhr nafli mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Dhuhr Nafl (Voluntary), facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Asr</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtil Asr sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Asr Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Asr</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtil Asr fardullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Asr Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>3 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ thalÄtha rak'Äti salÄtil Maghrib fardullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 3 units of Maghrib Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil Maghrib sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Maghrib Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Maghrib</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil Maghrib nafli mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Maghrib Nafl, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>4 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtil IshÄ' sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Isha Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>4 Rakat Fard</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ arba'a rak'Äti salÄtil IshÄ' fardullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 4 units of Isha Fard, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>2 Rakat Sunnah</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil IshÄ' sunnatu rasÅ«lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Isha Sunnah, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>3 Rakat Witr</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ thalÄtha rak'Äti salÄtil Witri wÄjibullÄhi ta'ÄlÄ mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 3 units of Witr Wajib, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Isha</td><td>2 Rakat Nafl</td><td>Nawaitu an usalliya lillÄhi ta'ÄlÄ rak'atai salÄtil IshÄ' nafli mutawajjihan ilÄ jihatil ka'batish sharÄ«fati, AllÄhu Akbar.</td><td>I turn to Allah the Most High with the intention to pray 2 units of Isha Nafl, facing the noble Ka'bah, Allah is Most Great.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n"
